{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778271436,"nonce":"EOlaFxruebKS6J8+OvprdWLqcqs=","message":"**Update — promoted; confirmed analytically load-bearing for Δv \u003e 0 signature.**\n\nThe C\u0026S analytical audit (\\`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/cs_alignment_audit.md\\`) decomposed the gap between rlrmp first-pass 8-state replication (+2.12%) and the MATLAB-faithful Python port (+8.24%, matching user-measured Fig 1e ~+7.76%):\n\n- Horizon n_steps (80 → 60): **−3.5% (largest factor)**\n- Q lag-block distribution + integrator weights (entries 6,7 = 0 → 1): −3.1%\n- (t/N)^6 cost cap (uncapped → \\`min(1, ...)\\`): ~−0.5%\n- τ (0.06 → 0.066) + minor: ~−0.5%\n\nSo the (t/N)^6 schedule + matched horizon together account for the bulk of the analytical Δv signature. Confirmed mechanism: terminal-time-concentrated penalty forces an aggressive early reach to \"buy time\" against late perturbations.\n\n**Implication for empirical studies:** rlrmp training currently uses uniform / hold-cost on a 1.3 s horizon, not (t/N)^6. The empirical Δv ≈ 0 we observe in trained controllers (synthesis §7) may therefore be **cost-function-induced** (controller not incentivised to rush to target before a terminal cliff) rather than **architecture-induced** (RNN-as-tracker decoupling per Gemini hypothesis tested in \\`8fcb6c7\\`). These two explanations are currently confounded.\n\n**Recommendation:** sweep (t/N)^α for α ∈ {0, 1, 2, 4, 6, 10} on matched-horizon training (60 steps + (t/N)^6 to mirror C\u0026S; also higher α with 1.3 s horizon to disambiguate horizon-vs-shape). Run alongside or before \\`8fcb6c7\\` (decoupling decomposition) so cost-effects and architecture-effects can be disambiguated. If under (t/N)^6 + 60 steps trained controllers recover Δv \u003e 0 across conditions, cost function is the dominant driver and decoupling story is weakened. If not, decoupling-via-architecture is the operative mechanism.\n\nThis issue should run after \\`efc4d68\\` (smoothness term, blocking on replicate-variance fix) but before / alongside \\`8fcb6c7\\`.\n\nCross-ref: training-methods coord \\`c99ad9d\\`, audit doc \\`/tmp/flavor_ab_review/findings/cs_alignment_audit.md\\`.","files":null}]}